```julia
function keep_only_names(words)
    return filter(word -> isuppercase(word[1]), words)
end
```

This function uses the `filter` function from Julia's standard library to create a new array containing only the words that start with an uppercase letter. The condition `isuppercase(word[1])` checks if the first character of each word is uppercase. The `filter` function applies this condition to each element of the `words` array and returns a new array with only the elements that satisfy the condition.
